g.text: - It stands for Continues Intigration and Continuoes Delivery.
- So In any organization we build a app, Now after building a app we have to give it to customer,
but before delivering the application some certain tests needs to be performed, like
Unit Testing, Security Scanning, Report Generation etc.
- Now this Steps are under Continuos delivery, and this are some steps that we create using tools like
- Before devops we use to do this things manually which would take months to just deliver the application to
the customer, so their was need to automate this process, so CI/CD came into the picture.
Standard Steps that we follow before delivering the application
Now If you need to develop and application or any feature, we just dont jump into the coding part.
What we do is we break the feature or Application into "Chunks" or Parts and we assign or store
- So when any developer gets that task or feature, he will setup the project on his local computer and start
- Once he is confident that the feature or application is ready, then he will push it to the VCS(Version Control System).
- The any "Push" or "Commit" happens in VCS then, automatically a CI/CD "Pipeline" is Triggered.
- And here all the steps will exceute on the code.
Some of the Tools that we use with CI/CD Pipeline.
